LinkMorph - URL Shortener Web App

LinkMorph is a full-stack URL shortener built using Node.js, Express, and MongoDB. It allows users to create, manage, and track shortened URLs while providing analytics for each link.

Features
âœ… User Authentication â€“ Secure login and registration for personalized dashboards
âœ… URL Shortening â€“ Easily shorten long URLs and get shareable links
âœ… Click Analytics â€“ Track the number of clicks for each shortened URL
âœ… User Dashboard â€“ Each user can view and manage their own links
âœ… Responsive UI â€“ Works seamlessly across all devices
âœ… Secure & Scalable â€“ Designed to handle high traffic efficiently


Tech Stack

Frontend: EJS, HTML, CSS
Backend: Node.js, Express.js
Database: MongoDB
Authentication: JWT (JSON Web Token)
Other: Mongoose, Bcrypt.js

Installation

1. Clone the repository:
git clone https://github.com/aditya-2145/LinkMorph.git
cd LinkMorph

2. Install dependencies:
npm install

3. Create a .env file and add the following variables:
MONGO_URI=your_mongodb_connection_string
JWT_SECRET=your_jwt_secret
BASE_URL=http://localhost:3000

4. Start the server:
npm start
Open http://localhost:3000 in your browser.


